Canada strongly condemned the recent suicide attack in Israel, emphasizing the importance of not derailing the Middle East peace process.
The attack, carried out by Palestinian militants, resulted in casualties and raised concerns about border security.
Various militant groups claimed responsibility, sparking confusion.
The Palestinian Authority also denounced the violence.
Israeli officials expressed fears of further attacks and emphasized the need for heightened security measures.
The incident reignited tensions in the region, prompting calls for continued dialogue and peace efforts.
The international community, including France, condemned the attack and urged a renewed focus on peace negotiations.
